<plot>Billy Reilly, the young son of a policeman, wants to enter a contest that offers a baseball glove for the best essay on an important person. As Billy is in the library, struggling to come up with an idea, a man suggests that he look around him instead of looking in books. Later, when Billy is playing ball with his friends, he accidentally breaks a window. Eventually this helps him learn a lesson that also gives him an idea for his essay.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?015209</url></doc>
